{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VA7ayXEjq4K94d7ACSb4Ex","type":"tool_result","content":"   297ŌåÆ### FR-9: Frontend ŌĆö Routes, Pages, and Components\n   298ŌåÆ\n   299ŌåÆAll frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n   300ŌåÆ\n   301ŌåÆ#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` ŌĆö Referral Link Handler\n   302ŌåÆ\n   303ŌåÆA lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n   304ŌåÆ\n   305ŌåÆ**Flow:**\n   306ŌåÆ1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n   307ŌåÆ2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n   308ŌåÆ3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   309ŌåÆ4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n   310ŌåÆ5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/apply` ŌåÆ clears localStorage on success\n   311ŌåÆ\n   312ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   313ŌåÆ- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   314ŌåÆ- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n   315ŌåÆ- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n   316ŌåÆ- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   317ŌåÆ- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n   318ŌåÆ- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n   319ŌåÆ\n   320ŌåÆ#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation ŌĆö Referrals Link\n   321ŌåÆ\n   322ŌåÆNew nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n   323ŌåÆ\n   324ŌåÆ```tsx\n   325ŌåÆ<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n   326ŌåÆ  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n   327ŌåÆ  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n   328ŌåÆ    {/* share/link icon */}\n   329ŌåÆ  </div>\n   330ŌåÆ  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n   331ŌåÆ</NavLink>\n   332ŌåÆ```\n   333ŌåÆ\n   334ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   335ŌåÆ- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n   336ŌåÆ- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   337ŌåÆ- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   338ŌåÆ- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   339ŌåÆ\n   340ŌåÆ#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n   341ŌåÆ\n   342ŌåÆMain referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n   343ŌåÆ\n   344ŌåÆ**Layout ŌĆö top to bottom:**\n   345ŌåÆ\n   346ŌåÆ1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   347ŌåÆ   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` ŌåÆ shows link\n   348ŌåÆ   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   349ŌåÆ   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   350ŌåÆ   - \"Change code\" link ŌåÆ inline edit field to set a new custom code ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n   351ŌåÆ\n   352ŌåÆ2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   353ŌåÆ   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   354ŌåÆ   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   355ŌåÆ   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports ŌåÆ SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   356ŌåÆ   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n   357ŌåÆ\n   358ŌåÆ3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   359ŌåÆ   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   360ŌåÆ   - \"Claim\" button ŌĆö enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   361ŌåÆ   - Claim flow: button ŌåÆ loading state ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/claim` ŌåÆ success toast with tx link ŌåÆ refresh stats\n   362ŌåÆ   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n   363ŌåÆ\n   364ŌåÆ4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   365ŌåÆ   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   366ŌåÆ   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   367ŌåÆ   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   368ŌåÆ   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n   369ŌåÆ\n   370ŌåÆ**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n   371ŌåÆ\n   372ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   373ŌåÆ- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   374ŌåÆ- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n   375ŌåÆ- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n   376ŌåÆ- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n   377ŌåÆ- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n   378ŌåÆ- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n   379ŌåÆ- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n   380ŌåÆ- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n   381ŌåÆ- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n   382ŌåÆ- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n   383ŌåÆ\n   384ŌåÆ#### 9d. Profile Settings ŌĆö Referral Code Input\n   385ŌåÆ\n   386ŌåÆIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n   387ŌåÆ\n   388ŌåÆ**Layout:**\n   389ŌåÆ- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n   390ŌåÆ- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n   391ŌåÆ- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n   392ŌåÆ- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n   393ŌåÆ\n   394ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   395ŌåÆ- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n   396ŌåÆ- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   397ŌåÆ- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   398ŌåÆ- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   399ŌåÆ- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   400ŌåÆ\n   401ŌåÆ#### 9e. API Client ŌĆö `lib/referral-api.ts`\n   402ŌåÆ\n   403ŌåÆThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n   404ŌåÆ\n   405ŌåÆ```typescript\n   406ŌåÆconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n   407ŌåÆ\n   408ŌåÆexport async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   409ŌåÆexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\n   410ŌåÆexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   411ŌåÆexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\n   412ŌåÆexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\n   413ŌåÆexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\n   414ŌåÆexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n   415ŌåÆ```\n   416ŌåÆ\n   417ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   418ŌåÆ- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n   419ŌåÆ- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   420ŌåÆ- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   421ŌåÆ- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   422ŌåÆ\n   423ŌåÆ#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook ŌĆö `useReferralApply`\n   424ŌåÆ\n   425ŌåÆA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n   426ŌåÆ\n   427ŌåÆ```typescript\n   428ŌåÆ// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\n   429ŌåÆexport function useReferralApply() {\n   430ŌåÆ  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n   431ŌåÆ  const { address } = useWallet();\n   432ŌåÆ\n   433ŌåÆ  useEffect(() => {\n   434ŌåÆ    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n   435ŌåÆ    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n   436ŌåÆ    if (!stored) return;\n   437ŌåÆ    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n   438ŌåÆ    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n   439ŌåÆ      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n   440ŌåÆ      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n   441ŌåÆ  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n   442ŌåÆ}\n   443ŌåÆ```\n   444ŌåÆ\n   445ŌåÆMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n   446ŌåÆ\n   447ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   448ŌåÆ- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   449ŌåÆ- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   450ŌåÆ- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   451ŌåÆ- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) ŌĆö retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   452ŌåÆ- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   453ŌåÆ- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   454ŌåÆ\n   455ŌåÆ### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n   456ŌåÆ\n   457ŌåÆThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n   458ŌåÆ\n   459ŌåÆ**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n   460ŌåÆ1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n   461ŌåÆ2. If referrer exists ŌåÆ calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports ├Ś referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports ├Ś fee_bps / 10000)\n   462ŌåÆ3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n   463ŌåÆ4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n   464ŌåÆ\n   465ŌåÆ**Referrer rate lookup:**\n   466ŌåÆ1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n   467ŌåÆ2. If found ŌåÆ use KOL rate\n   468ŌåÆ3. If not ŌåÆ use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   469ŌåÆ\n   470ŌåÆ**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n   471ŌåÆ\n   472ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   473ŌåÆ- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n   474ŌåÆ- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n   475ŌåÆ- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n   476ŌåÆ- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n   477ŌåÆ- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n   478ŌåÆ- [ ] No additional RPC calls ŌĆö purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n   479ŌåÆ- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n   480ŌåÆ\n   481ŌåÆ---\n   482ŌåÆ\n   483ŌåÆ### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n   484ŌåÆ\n   485ŌåÆReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n   486ŌåÆ\n   487ŌåÆ**Event types (v1):**\n   488ŌåÆ- `referral.claim_requested` ŌĆö emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n   489ŌåÆ\n   490ŌåÆNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings ŌĆö only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n   491ŌåÆ\n   492ŌåÆ**Payload contract:**\n   493ŌåÆ\n   494ŌåÆ`referral.claim_requested`\n   495ŌåÆ```json\n   496ŌåÆ{"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a51b6cb4-cdb0-4e97-8a06-1ab74eb394f9","uuid":"4d623c09-48d5-48c2-b586-0150acd6ac62","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:06:06.432Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"### FR-9: Frontend ŌĆö Routes, Pages, and Components\n\nAll frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n\n#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` ŌĆö Referral Link Handler\n\nA lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/apply` ŌåÆ clears localStorage on success\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n\n#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation ŌĆö Referrals Link\n\nNew nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n\n```tsx\n<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n    {/* share/link icon */}\n  </div>\n  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n</NavLink>\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n\nMain referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n\n**Layout ŌĆö top to bottom:**\n\n1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` ŌåÆ shows link\n   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   - \"Change code\" link ŌåÆ inline edit field to set a new custom code ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n\n2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports ŌåÆ SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n\n3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   - \"Claim\" button ŌĆö enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   - Claim flow: button ŌåÆ loading state ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/claim` ŌåÆ success toast with tx link ŌåÆ refresh stats\n   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n\n4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n\n**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n\n#### 9d. Profile Settings ŌĆö Referral Code Input\n\nIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n\n**Layout:**\n- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9e. API Client ŌĆö `lib/referral-api.ts`\n\nThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n\n```typescript\nconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n\nexport async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\nexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\nexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\nexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\nexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook ŌĆö `useReferralApply`\n\nA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n\n```typescript\n// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\nexport function useReferralApply() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n  const { address } = useWallet();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n    if (!stored) return;\n    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n}\n```\n\nMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) ŌĆö retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\nThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n\n**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n2. If referrer exists ŌåÆ calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports ├Ś referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports ├Ś fee_bps / 10000)\n3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n\n**Referrer rate lookup:**\n1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n2. If found ŌåÆ use KOL rate\n3. If not ŌåÆ use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n\n**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n- [ ] No additional RPC calls ŌĆö purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n\n---\n\n### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n\nReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n\n**Event types (v1):**\n- `referral.claim_requested` ŌĆö emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n\nNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings ŌĆö only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n\n**Payload contract:**\n\n`referral.claim_requested`\n```json\n{","numLines":200,"startLine":297,"totalLines":715}}}
