{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TYzSueEpb1an1VSx8GQ5fA","type":"tool_result","content":"   497ŌåÆ  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n   498ŌåÆ  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n   499ŌåÆ  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n   500ŌåÆ  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n   501ŌåÆ}\n   502ŌåÆ```\n   503ŌåÆ\n   504ŌåÆ**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n   505ŌåÆ\n   506ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   507ŌåÆ- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n   508ŌåÆ- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n   509ŌåÆ- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   510ŌåÆ- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   511ŌåÆ- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   512ŌåÆ- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   513ŌåÆ\n   514ŌåÆ---\n   515ŌåÆ\n   516ŌåÆ## Design Decisions (v1)\n   517ŌåÆ\n   518ŌåÆ### Why immutable referrer linkage\n   519ŌåÆ\n   520ŌåÆ- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n   521ŌåÆ- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n   522ŌåÆ- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n   523ŌåÆ\n   524ŌåÆ### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n   525ŌåÆ\n   526ŌåÆ- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n   527ŌåÆ- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n   528ŌåÆ- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n   529ŌåÆ\n   530ŌåÆ### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n   531ŌåÆ\n   532ŌåÆ- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n   533ŌåÆ- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n   534ŌåÆ- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n   535ŌåÆ\n   536ŌåÆ---\n   537ŌåÆ\n   538ŌåÆ## Success Criteria\n   539ŌåÆ\n   540ŌåÆ- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n   541ŌåÆ- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   542ŌåÆ- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n   543ŌåÆ- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n   544ŌåÆ- No on-chain program changes required ŌĆö entirely off-chain for v1\n   545ŌåÆ- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n   546ŌåÆ- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n   547ŌåÆ\n   548ŌåÆ---\n   549ŌåÆ\n   550ŌåÆ## Dependencies\n   551ŌåÆ\n   552ŌåÆ- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n   553ŌåÆ- **Async event queue (spec 301)** ŌĆö referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n   554ŌåÆ- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n   555ŌåÆ- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n   556ŌåÆ- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n   557ŌåÆ- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n   558ŌåÆ\n   559ŌåÆ## Assumptions\n   560ŌåÆ\n   561ŌåÆ- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n   562ŌåÆ- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n   563ŌåÆ- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n   564ŌåÆ- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n   565ŌåÆ- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ ŌĆö already met)\n   566ŌåÆ\n   567ŌåÆ---\n   568ŌåÆ\n   569ŌåÆ## Validation Plan\n   570ŌåÆ\n   571ŌåÆ| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   572ŌåÆ|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   573ŌåÆ| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n   574ŌåÆ| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n   575ŌåÆ| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n   576ŌåÆ| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n   577ŌåÆ| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n   578ŌåÆ| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n   579ŌåÆ| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n   580ŌåÆ| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n   581ŌåÆ| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n   582ŌåÆ| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n   583ŌåÆ| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n   584ŌåÆ| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n   585ŌåÆ| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim ŌåÆ poll status ŌåÆ verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n   586ŌåÆ| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code ŌåÆ verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n   587ŌåÆ| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n   588ŌåÆ| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n   589ŌåÆ| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n   590ŌåÆ| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n   591ŌåÆ| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n   592ŌåÆ| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n   593ŌåÆ| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n   594ŌåÆ| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n   595ŌåÆ| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n   596ŌåÆ\n   597ŌåÆ---\n   598ŌåÆ\n   599ŌåÆ## Completion Signal\n   600ŌåÆ\n   601ŌåÆ### Implementation Checklist\n   602ŌåÆ\n   603ŌåÆ#### Prerequisite\n   604ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] Event queue infrastructure implemented per spec 301 (completed in spec 301)\n   605ŌåÆ\n   606ŌåÆ#### Backend ŌĆö Database & Core\n   607ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`: create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables with all constraints and indexes per FR-8 (done: iteration 1)\n   608ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD (done: iteration 3)\n   609ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries (done: iteration 4)\n   610ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance(wallet)` (sum referrer_earned where wallet=referrer + sum referee_rebate where wallet=referee, minus completed claims), `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`, `getReferralStats(wallet)` (done: iteration 5)\n   611ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)` (check kol_rates, fallback to env default) (done: iteration 6)\n   612ŌåÆ\n   613ŌåÆ#### Backend ŌĆö API Endpoints\n   614ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` ŌĆö set player-chosen code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, unique). Requires JWT auth. Returns `{ code, url }` (FR-1, FR-7) (done: iteration 7)\n   615ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` ŌĆö return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404 (FR-7) (done: iteration 8)\n   616ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` ŌĆö link referee to referrer. Validate: code exists, no self-referral, no existing referrer. Returns `{ referrer, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }` (FR-2, FR-7) (done: iteration 9)\n   617ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` ŌĆö return referredCount, activeCount (7d), totalVolumeLamports, totalEarnedLamports, pendingLamports for authenticated wallet. All values as lamport strings (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 10)\n   618ŌåÆ- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` ŌĆö paginated per-game earnings log with roundId, gameType, refereeWallet, wagerLamports, earnedLamports, createdAt. Query params: page, limit (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 11)\n   619ŌåÆ- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` ŌĆö validate pending balance > min threshold (env `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default 10M = 0.01 SOL), snapshot amount, insert claim row + emit `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB tx. Return 202 `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` (FR-6, FR-7)\n   620ŌåÆ- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` ŌĆö return claim status + txSignature if completed (FR-7)\n   621ŌåÆ- [ ] [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware\n   622ŌåÆ\n   623ŌåÆ#### Backend ŌĆö Settlement Integration\n   624ŌåÆ- [ ] [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: after each game settlement DB write, check `referral_links` for the settled player(s). If referrer exists, calculate `referrer_earned = fee_lamports * referrer_rate_bps / 10000` and `referee_rebate = fee_lamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%). Insert into `referral_earnings` in the same DB transaction. Use `getReferrerRate(wallet)` for KOL override (FR-4, FR-10)\n   625ŌåÆ- [ ] [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity ŌĆö referral earning insert MUST be in the same transaction as the game settlement update (FR-10 + System Invariant 4)\n   626ŌåÆ\n   627ŌåÆ#### Backend ŌĆö Claim Queue Handler\n   628ŌåÆ- [ ] [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry: load claim by ID, verify status is `pending`, update to `processing`, re-verify available balance >= claim amount, execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to wallet, record tx_signature, update status to `completed`. On failure: record error, update status to `failed`. Idempotent: skip if status is already `completed` (FR-6, FR-11)\n   629ŌåÆ\n   630ŌåÆ#### Frontend ŌĆö API Client & Plumbing\n   631ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` ŌĆö 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth following `auth-api.ts` pattern: `setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus` (FR-9e)\n   632ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` ŌĆö capture code to `localStorage` key `referral_code` as `{ code, capturedAt }`, redirect to `/` via `<Navigate replace />` (FR-9a)\n   633ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook ŌĆö on authentication, if `referral_code` in localStorage and user has no referrer, call `POST /referral/apply`. Clear localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid/already linked). Keep on transient failure. Show success toast. Mount in `App.tsx` inside auth provider tree (FR-9f)\n   634ŌåÆ\n   635ŌåÆ#### Frontend ŌĆö Referral Page\n   636ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] Sidebar nav item \"Referrals\" in Player section of `Sidebar.tsx` with share/link icon, `--nc: var(--color-green)`, navigates to `/referrals` (FR-9b)\n   637ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] `/referrals` route + `ReferralPage` shell: unauthenticated state shows connect-wallet prompt with referral program description. Authenticated state renders feature sections. Wrap in `RouteErrorBoundary` (FR-9c)\n   638ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] Referral page ┬¦1: \"Your Referral Link\" card ŌĆö custom code input (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button (if none), display code + full URL + Copy Link button with clipboard feedback. \"Change code\" option with inline validation (FR-9c ┬¦1)\n   639ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] Referral page ┬¦2: Stats summary card ŌĆö four stat boxes (Referred Players, Active 7d, Total Volume, Total Earned) from `GET /referral/stats`. SOL values via lamportsŌåÆSOL formatting. Loading skeleton (FR-9c ┬¦2)\n   640ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] Referral page ┬¦3: Pending balance card ŌĆö show unified pending balance prominently. Breakdown: \"From referrals: X SOL\" + \"From fee rebates: Y SOL\". Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with Solana explorer tx link (FR-9c ┬¦3, FR-6)\n   641ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] Referral page ┬¦4: Earnings history table ŌĆö paginated from `GET /referral/earnings`. Columns: Date, Game, Referee (truncated wallet), Wager, Your Earning. Empty state message. Pagination controls (FR-9c ┬¦4)\n   642ŌåÆ- [ ] [frontend] Profile settings: \"Referral Code\" section in profile settings tab. If no referrer: input + Apply button. If already referred: read-only \"Referred by: [wallet]\". Error states inline (FR-9d)\n   643ŌåÆ\n   644ŌåÆ#### Testing\n   645ŌåÆ- [ ] [test] Backend unit tests for referral routes: set custom code (happy path + validation + uniqueness), apply (happy path + self-referral + duplicate), stats, earnings pagination, claim flow (happy + zero balance + below threshold + concurrent)\n   646ŌåÆ- [ ] [test] Backend integration test: settle a game for a referred player ŌåÆ verify `referral_earnings` row with correct referrer_earned + referee_rebate amounts\n   647ŌåÆ- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n   648ŌåÆ- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   649ŌåÆ- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for `/referrals` page (new page) and sidebar (new nav item). Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) ŌåÆ commit; **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) ŌåÆ save diff images to `docs/specs/300-referral-system/visual-review/`, describe concerns; **FAIL** ŌåÆ fix code\n   650ŌåÆ- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is included, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n   651ŌåÆ\n   652ŌåÆ### Testing Requirements\n   653ŌåÆ\n   654ŌåÆThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   655ŌåÆ\n   656ŌåÆ#### Code Quality\n   657ŌåÆ- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   658ŌåÆ- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n   659ŌåÆ- [ ] No lint errors\n   660ŌåÆ\n   661ŌåÆ#### Functional Verification\n   662ŌåÆ- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   663ŌåÆ- [ ] Edge cases handled\n   664ŌåÆ- [ ] Error states handled\n   665ŌåÆ\n   666ŌåÆ#### Visual Regression\n   667ŌåÆ- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n   668ŌåÆ- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n   669ŌåÆ- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n   670ŌåÆ- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are included\n   671ŌåÆ\n   672ŌåÆ#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n   673ŌåÆ- [ ] Desktop view correct\n   674ŌåÆ- [ ] Mobile view correct\n   675ŌåÆ\n   676ŌåÆ#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n   677ŌåÆ- [ ] No JS console errors\n   678ŌåÆ- [ ] No failed network requests\n   679ŌåÆ\n   680ŌåÆ#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n   681ŌåÆ\n   682ŌåÆBefore declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\n   683ŌåÆmakes sense from a player's perspective.\n   684ŌåÆ\n   685ŌåÆ- [ ] Set custom referral code ŌåÆ copy link ŌåÆ verify URL format\n   686ŌåÆ- [ ] Visit referral link in incognito ŌåÆ authenticate ŌåÆ verify referrer linked\n   687ŌåÆ- [ ] Manually enter code in settings ŌåÆ verify referrer linked\n   688ŌåÆ- [ ] Play a game as referred player ŌåÆ verify referrer earnings appear\n   689ŌåÆ- [ ] Referrer dashboard shows correct stats\n   690ŌåÆ- [ ] Claim earnings ŌåÆ verify SOL arrives in wallet\n   691ŌåÆ- [ ] Attempt self-referral ŌåÆ verify blocked\n   692ŌåÆ- [ ] Attempt to change referrer ŌåÆ verify blocked\n   693ŌåÆ- [ ] Referee fee rebate accrues after playing a game (visible in pending balance)\n   694ŌåÆ- [ ] Referral page shows breakdown: \"From referrals: X\" + \"From fee rebates: Y\"\n   695ŌåÆ\n   696ŌåÆ### Iteration Instructions"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a51b6cb4-cdb0-4e97-8a06-1ab74eb394f9","uuid":"75bf54e1-8507-4187-a39e-a5e6205a9d0d","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:06:12.214Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions (v1)\n\n### Why immutable referrer linkage\n\n- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n\n### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n\n- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n\n### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n\n- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n- No on-chain program changes required ŌĆö entirely off-chain for v1\n- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n- **Async event queue (spec 301)** ŌĆö referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ ŌĆö already met)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim ŌåÆ poll status ŌåÆ verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code ŌåÆ verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n#### Prerequisite\n- [x] [backend] Event queue infrastructure implemented per spec 301 (completed in spec 301)\n\n#### Backend ŌĆö Database & Core\n- [x] [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`: create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables with all constraints and indexes per FR-8 (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD (done: iteration 3)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance(wallet)` (sum referrer_earned where wallet=referrer + sum referee_rebate where wallet=referee, minus completed claims), `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`, `getReferralStats(wallet)` (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)` (check kol_rates, fallback to env default) (done: iteration 6)\n\n#### Backend ŌĆö API Endpoints\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` ŌĆö set player-chosen code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, unique). Requires JWT auth. Returns `{ code, url }` (FR-1, FR-7) (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` ŌĆö return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404 (FR-7) (done: iteration 8)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` ŌĆö link referee to referrer. Validate: code exists, no self-referral, no existing referrer. Returns `{ referrer, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }` (FR-2, FR-7) (done: iteration 9)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` ŌĆö return referredCount, activeCount (7d), totalVolumeLamports, totalEarnedLamports, pendingLamports for authenticated wallet. All values as lamport strings (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 10)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` ŌĆö paginated per-game earnings log with roundId, gameType, refereeWallet, wagerLamports, earnedLamports, createdAt. Query params: page, limit (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 11)\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` ŌĆö validate pending balance > min threshold (env `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default 10M = 0.01 SOL), snapshot amount, insert claim row + emit `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB tx. Return 202 `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` (FR-6, FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` ŌĆö return claim status + txSignature if completed (FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware\n\n#### Backend ŌĆö Settlement Integration\n- [ ] [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: after each game settlement DB write, check `referral_links` for the settled player(s). If referrer exists, calculate `referrer_earned = fee_lamports * referrer_rate_bps / 10000` and `referee_rebate = fee_lamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%). Insert into `referral_earnings` in the same DB transaction. Use `getReferrerRate(wallet)` for KOL override (FR-4, FR-10)\n- [ ] [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity ŌĆö referral earning insert MUST be in the same transaction as the game settlement update (FR-10 + System Invariant 4)\n\n#### Backend ŌĆö Claim Queue Handler\n- [ ] [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry: load claim by ID, verify status is `pending`, update to `processing`, re-verify available balance >= claim amount, execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to wallet, record tx_signature, update status to `completed`. On failure: record error, update status to `failed`. Idempotent: skip if status is already `completed` (FR-6, FR-11)\n\n#### Frontend ŌĆö API Client & Plumbing\n- [ ] [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` ŌĆö 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth following `auth-api.ts` pattern: `setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus` (FR-9e)\n- [ ] [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` ŌĆö capture code to `localStorage` key `referral_code` as `{ code, capturedAt }`, redirect to `/` via `<Navigate replace />` (FR-9a)\n- [ ] [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook ŌĆö on authentication, if `referral_code` in localStorage and user has no referrer, call `POST /referral/apply`. Clear localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid/already linked). Keep on transient failure. Show success toast. Mount in `App.tsx` inside auth provider tree (FR-9f)\n\n#### Frontend ŌĆö Referral Page\n- [ ] [frontend] Sidebar nav item \"Referrals\" in Player section of `Sidebar.tsx` with share/link icon, `--nc: var(--color-green)`, navigates to `/referrals` (FR-9b)\n- [ ] [frontend] `/referrals` route + `ReferralPage` shell: unauthenticated state shows connect-wallet prompt with referral program description. Authenticated state renders feature sections. Wrap in `RouteErrorBoundary` (FR-9c)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page ┬¦1: \"Your Referral Link\" card ŌĆö custom code input (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button (if none), display code + full URL + Copy Link button with clipboard feedback. \"Change code\" option with inline validation (FR-9c ┬¦1)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page ┬¦2: Stats summary card ŌĆö four stat boxes (Referred Players, Active 7d, Total Volume, Total Earned) from `GET /referral/stats`. SOL values via lamportsŌåÆSOL formatting. Loading skeleton (FR-9c ┬¦2)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page ┬¦3: Pending balance card ŌĆö show unified pending balance prominently. Breakdown: \"From referrals: X SOL\" + \"From fee rebates: Y SOL\". Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with Solana explorer tx link (FR-9c ┬¦3, FR-6)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page ┬¦4: Earnings history table ŌĆö paginated from `GET /referral/earnings`. Columns: Date, Game, Referee (truncated wallet), Wager, Your Earning. Empty state message. Pagination controls (FR-9c ┬¦4)\n- [ ] [frontend] Profile settings: \"Referral Code\" section in profile settings tab. If no referrer: input + Apply button. If already referred: read-only \"Referred by: [wallet]\". Error states inline (FR-9d)\n\n#### Testing\n- [ ] [test] Backend unit tests for referral routes: set custom code (happy path + validation + uniqueness), apply (happy path + self-referral + duplicate), stats, earnings pagination, claim flow (happy + zero balance + below threshold + concurrent)\n- [ ] [test] Backend integration test: settle a game for a referred player ŌåÆ verify `referral_earnings` row with correct referrer_earned + referee_rebate amounts\n- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for `/referrals` page (new page) and sidebar (new nav item). Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) ŌåÆ commit; **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) ŌåÆ save diff images to `docs/specs/300-referral-system/visual-review/`, describe concerns; **FAIL** ŌåÆ fix code\n- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is included, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n- [ ] No lint errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Edge cases handled\n- [ ] Error states handled\n\n#### Visual Regression\n- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are included\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] Desktop view correct\n- [ ] Mobile view correct\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No JS console errors\n- [ ] No failed network requests\n\n#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n\nBefore declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\nmakes sense from a player's perspective.\n\n- [ ] Set custom referral code ŌåÆ copy link ŌåÆ verify URL format\n- [ ] Visit referral link in incognito ŌåÆ authenticate ŌåÆ verify referrer linked\n- [ ] Manually enter code in settings ŌåÆ verify referrer linked\n- [ ] Play a game as referred player ŌåÆ verify referrer earnings appear\n- [ ] Referrer dashboard shows correct stats\n- [ ] Claim earnings ŌåÆ verify SOL arrives in wallet\n- [ ] Attempt self-referral ŌåÆ verify blocked\n- [ ] Attempt to change referrer ŌåÆ verify blocked\n- [ ] Referee fee rebate accrues after playing a game (visible in pending balance)\n- [ ] Referral page shows breakdown: \"From referrals: X\" + \"From fee rebates: Y\"\n\n### Iteration Instructions","numLines":200,"startLine":497,"totalLines":715}}}
