{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VrdDqAhMuAGPDL8ByWc5Nc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here are the relevant code sections from the file:\n\n## 1. ReferralClaim Interface (lines 168-177)\n```typescript\nexport interface ReferralClaim {\n  id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  amount_lamports: string;\n  status: \"pending\" | \"processing\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\";\n  tx_signature: string | null;\n  error: string | null;\n  requested_at: Date;\n  processed_at: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\n## 2. insertReferralClaim Method Implementation (lines 928-935)\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralClaim(wallet, amountLamports) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralClaim[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_claims (wallet, amount_lamports, status)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, ${amountLamports}, 'pending')\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n},\n```\n\n## 3. getPendingBalance Method Implementation (lines 852-872)\n```typescript\nasync getPendingBalance(wallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<{ pending: string }[]>`\n    SELECT COALESCE(\n      (\n        SELECT SUM(referrer_earned_lamports)\n        FROM referral_earnings WHERE referrer_wallet = ${wallet}\n      ), 0\n    ) + COALESCE(\n      (\n        SELECT SUM(referee_rebate_lamports)\n        FROM referral_earnings WHERE referee_wallet = ${wallet}\n      ), 0\n    ) - COALESCE(\n      (\n        SELECT SUM(amount_lamports)\n        FROM referral_claims WHERE wallet = ${wallet} AND status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed')\n      ), 0\n    ) AS pending\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!.pending;\n},\n```\n\n## 4. Config Interface for referral settings\n**Not found in this file.** The file does not contain `referralMinClaimLamports` or `referralDefaultRateBps` config interfaces. These are likely defined in a separate config file (possibly `config.ts`, `env.ts`, or a types file in a sibling directory).\n\n## 5. Transaction Patterns\n**No `sql.begin` or `sql.transaction`